  <!-- MESSAGES -->
  <string name="how_to_add_reader_html">
    <![CDATA[
    <h3>Audio Format</h3>
    <p>
      Only Ogg Vorbis is supported．mono audio with 22050 Hz is recommended.<br/>
      You have to somehow get 202 ogg files which 1st and 2nd half of the poem is recorded separately from 101 poems (+1 is for Joka).
    </p>
    <h3>File Name Convention</h3>
    <p>
      Rename each file to <tt><font color="#FFFF00">[Reciter]_[Poem No.]_[1st=1,2nd=2].ogg</font></tt><br/>
      , where some zeros must be padded to fit three digits. Poem number of Joka is 000.<br/>
      (Example: 2nd half of `Hototogisu` read by Inaba &rArr; <tt><font color="#FFFF00">inaba_081_2.ogg</font></tt>)
    </p>
    <h3>Where to Place</h3>
    <p>
      (1) Make folder named <tt><font color="#FFFF00">wasuramoti_reader</font></tt> inside SD card or internal storage. Note: do not make it in a folder which is too deep.
    </p>
    <p>
      (2) Make folder named <tt><font color="#FFFF00">[Reciter]</font></tt>, and place 202 ogg files in it.
    </p>
    <p>
      (Example: 1st half of `Hananoiroha` read by Inaba &rArr; <tt><font color="#FFFF00">wasuramoti_reader/inaba/inaba_009_1.ogg</font></tt>)<br/><br/>
      Now new reader should be added to choices in this app.
    </p>
    ]]>
  </string>
